# CI & smoke

## GitHub Actions

- Use `pnpm/action-setup@v4` **without** a `version:` key — read `packageManager` from root `package.json` (`pnpm@11.3.0`).
- Node 22; `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`.
- Workflows: `.github/workflows/ci.yml` (smoke matrix, web build, helm lint), `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` (optional path filter).

## Typecheck (`pnpm typecheck:ci`)

- Checks an allowlist of leaf packages in `scripts/typecheck.ts` (expand as `core` / `api` debt is fixed).
- CI job: `typecheck` in `.github/workflows/ci.yml`.

## Smoke (`pnpm smoke`)

- End-to-end platform guarantee in **local** mode (no vendor accounts required).
- Registers example agent, exercises dispatcher, MCP, budgets, billing free tier, SAML session, eval gate, E2B mock.
- **Must stay green** before merging platform changes.

## When CI fails

- Reproduce locally: `pnpm smoke` or `RUNTIME=e2b E2B_MOCK=true pnpm smoke`.
- Web build: `pnpm --filter @platform/web build` with `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_KEY` set.

## Hooks (optional)

If the user repeatedly asks to run smoke after edits, suggest `.cursor/hooks.json` (see skill `suggesting-cursor-hooks`).
